---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Home">
  <main class="hero">
    <h1 class="teal-name">Sofia Voumvourakis</h1>
    <div class="divider"></div>
    <p class="intro-text">
      Hello! I’m a government and data science student who often finds herself asking: 
      <span class="teal-quote">“To advance humanity, are we losing it?”</span> 
      I am driven to build a future where technology governance is resilient and equitable. 
      Beyond the screen, I’m creative at heart—dabbling in poetry and art—and curious 
      in practice—exploring philosophy, psychology, and global perspectives.
    </p>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero {
    height: 70vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0 15%;
  }
  .teal-name {
    color: var(--bright-teal);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 10vw, 6rem);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .divider {
    width: 60px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border-color);
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }
  .intro-text {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 700px;
  }
  .teal-quote {
    color: var(--bright-teal);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>